text: I just enjoy how Saffron Olive rt'd it. Because that's so surprising. And I love how she singled out CFB as the ones taking in the responsibility for it. We know WotC won't give 2 poops, but CFB probably is secretly like "don't bring us into this talk again"
I just dont buy this whole make the game accessible thing. I think they can make standard cheaper in general, but abolishing RL so legacy is more accessible? Wtf?
Like its ok to have something thats harder to access. Makes it more fun to find it

My big thing is conflating price with accessibility. Anyone can go to tcg and buy them, they not cut off from access. The price is what's holding them back, but it's not like you can't find people selling them. Attainability is what I think people are trying to fight, not accessibility

Most stores let people play full-proxy legacy, at least around here. And still nobody shows up. I'm fairly sure abolishing the RL so people can spend a mere 500 dollars on a deck will get them to show for a format they won't show to play 0 dollar decks.
Why not spend that energy on campaigning WotC to make cards of equivalent power?
I don't even really care for cards of equivalent power myself, but I'm almost exclusively and EDH player where adding one Tundra to your W/U list makes a difference maybe 1 out of 100 games
Yea, what Dana said.

Plus, the people who tout edh as a causal format are also the ones who at least I see bitching the most about duals. But if the format is casual, why do you need the best of everything? Seems rather competitive of them....
It's not as if standard is cheap. The same people cool with running 4 $25 Gideons in their standard deck piss and moan about the cost of a Serra's Sanctum for EDH
Not really. It's still not as bad as that rally the ancestors 4c goodstuff format though
Those same people bitching about their standard being expensive probably sold their fetches to buy into new standard too though.
It's all anecdotal though, every area is different so there's no way we will ever get real data on any of this

Because as you age with the game power creep is inevitable but that misses the point if other folks’ goal is to play Legacy, which we all agree is a false premise. More importantly there are more than duals on the RL.
We have seen a couple RL workaround cards lately. Cryptolith Rites and Ikea's Cradle off the top of my head
"But snew duels!"
WotC can reprint shocks whenever they want and those, for EDH, are equivalent to duals.

One of these days I hope we get to trigger jason in every way before his daughter has her first bottle. some hokey reserve list tweet, the Blackhawks trade away Kane and Toews, Miller High Life wins some sort of beer award...
The Champaign of beers.
Grain Belt Premium. Best beer of the north.
I can see his eye twitching already.
Saffron Olive is a MODO exclusive player, anyway. He shouldn't even be allowed to have an opinion about the RL
Who gives a shit what MODO players think about paper cards?
But duals cost sooooo many tickets, <@U32LRG9NU>! Tickets!
Whatever ever happened to Travis Woo?
He said Hitler did nothing wrong and got shitcanned
Seriously?
Well that would explain why I never see his name anymore
Who?
Exactly
Surprised he's not working in the White House now
He's not white
Fair
who the hell is travis woo
He was a saffron olive-ish brewer who made wonky semi-effective decks
I can't tell if we're doing a bit because he's been forgotten or if we never knew who he was
Had to go do a search for Travis Woo Hitler and the video is on yourtube. He's playing modo and just casually talking about Mein Kampf
It was a "thought experiment" guys! Or however he tried to sluff it off
I missed that whole thing, so bizarre. It was only in talking about Seth today that I realized I hadn't seen anyone mention Woo in forever. Guess now I know why.
Never go full PewDiePie
Yikes... “The Germans got sucked into WWI and weren’t really the aggressors, but they were winning the war...”
What did he do? I don't pay attention to Internet personalities, so I only know what you mentioned for a second on money draught that he even exists
PDP dropped a hard N word on stream
Oh
it "slipped out"
Well that would do it
Yea that does "slip" out
He's got a past history of sketchy shit though
So it's not like it's a one-time thing in PDP's case
Plus he's a fucking hack
Jesus  I’m watching one of the Travis Woo videos and what’s scarier are the comments, all which say “Nothing wrong here...I agree 100%...”
People are the worst.
Indeed

I remember seeing a little bit of the video, I understand what he was trying to do and I don't think it was as malicious as it sounded, if it was at all, but he didn't go about it well at all. He wasn't really using the platform for it. But yea the people in the comments running with it are way worse. It shouldn't have happened to begin with because it wasn't something worth exploring in the first place
It didn’t help that he was wrong about so much of his interpretation...

That too. In my mind is biggest mistake was a lack of judgement even going into it to begin with. I'm not sure if he really believes what he came up with having seen a few of his other videos which are a far cry from what I did see him talk about, but I do think there were morons in the comments who do agree with the sketchy stuff he talked about
That’s the really scary part.
Yup.
WWI, maybe. WWII was a whole other thing.
No...sorry, they were the aggressors in WWI, the treaties were a pretext.
I'm no great history buff. I just listen to hardcore history.
I like Hardcore History, but I wind up listening to the Dollop way more
I just wonder how much TWoo realizes his life would be VERY different if what he pondered was true.
I tried the dollop, but couldn't get into it.
The stories are almost always horrifying
And it helps if you appreciate Dave Anthony's black sense of humor
I'm all about dark humor, but they didn't really grab me.
Give it one more try sometime and try the episode the Rube
A pitcher as good as Cy Young who chased firetrucks like a dog, it's pretty great
In a game he made his outfielders come into the infield grass and sit down so he could strike out the guy at the plate
The Dollop was okay.
But they came out too frequently for me to want to keep up with it.
They're down to one a week, but yeah, two was a lot
